          <h1><span style="color:rgb(173, 11, 11);">Week 2:</span>
            Still Guessing...</h1>
          <p>
            Yep, we're still guessing. While we're not 100% sure about all the
            functionalities we'll include in our GuessMaster Webgame, we can
            tell you this: It'll be a fun minigame!
            <br />
            Starting from our landing page our players will have to add their
            name (or alias) and can then choose from one of three options. When
            clicking on "Quick Game" they either join an ongoing public game or
            a public lobby with predefined settings will be opened. Joining a
            private game for guessing with e.g. friends or colleagues is easy,
            all you need to know is a code, enter it in the textbox and click on
            "Join now". If a player wants to create a lobby with custom
            settings, he/she can do so by simply clicking on the corresponding
            button. The player will then have some options, including the
            possibility to choose between a public or private game.
            <br />
            We'll continue explaining one of the other Mockups in our next blog
            entry.
            <br /><br />
            In the past weeks we also used our time to get to know our tool of
            choice, unity. Each of us started off with a tutorial and then
            continued developing a simple something in Unity.
            <br />
            In our ongoing sprint we created and refined our Use Case and
            finished our first Mockups. You'll find a Mockup of our landingpage
            down below.
