          <h1><span style="color:rgb(173, 11, 11);">Week 4:</span>
            Time for another Update</h1>
          <p>
            This week we finished our class diagram (attached below) and made
            some small adjustments to our sequence diagrams. The adjustments
            were so minor that it wouldn't justify displaying them here, so
            please go check them out at our GitHub if you're interested in those
            details.
            <br />
            We used the OCP (Open-Closed Principle) for our design as it is the
            most fitting one for a game as it is open for additions while not
            allowing changes in the "running" program.
            <br />
            Our most important class is the "LobbyController" because of its
            necessity for joining and creating a game. It is also worth
            mentioning that none of the classes is completely finished as of now
            because we're not absolutely sure about all the functions we
            require.
            <br /><br />
